01
November
UBA Staff Jog to Bond

Staff and Management of UBA (Ghana) last Saturday took to the streets of Accra, Kumasi and Takoradi in their maiden ‘jogging to bond’ exercise. Cladded in red lacoste ‘T’ shirts and face caps, the UBA family virtually painted the principal streets in the 3 cities red.

Dubbed 'Jogging to bond', over 400 members partook in the Saturday morning fun jog simulataneosly in Accra, Kumasi and Takoradi. According to Sanusi Mudasiru, Chief Operating Officer at UBA who led the management team, the jogging exercise was part of the bank’s strategy to build team spirit through exciting sporting and athletic activities. He also mentioned that the exercise was a practice conducted across the UBA Group for staff members so they can keep fit and healthy.

The Accra event which took-off from the Aviation social centre in Accra at 7am saw members walk over a 7km stretch to the 37 military hospital – Ako adjei circle and Danquah circles through cantonment. When members convened at the centre after the walk, they were treated to exciting aerobic session and fun-filled sporting activities. The UBA staff also celebrated the birthday of November birthday celebrants by cutting a special birthday cake decorated in their honour.

Nana Kyeremateng, Head of Corporate Communications at UBA mentioned that the maiden event was a resounding success as colleagues came out in their numbers. He said that the event provided the opportunity for colleagues to foster new friendships and meet exciting people outside their office. According to him, the fun jog will become a monthly event which shall be held concurrently across geographical locations where UBA has presence.

October
UBA Launches 3 Moneygram Redshops

UBA Ghana has introduced another industry first by launching the first ever Moneygram redshop in Ghana.The Moneygram redshop is a seperate banking hall dedicated exclusively for Moneygram money transfer recipientsIt constitutes a separate banking hall within designated UBA branch locations to carry out Moneygram transactions. The new redshops which are located in Madina, Ring-road and Abosey-Okai are housed in the already existing UBA branches.
Speaking at the press Launch held at the Madina branch, Sanusi Mudasiru - Chief Operating Officer at UBA, mentioned that the purpose of creating exclusivity for Moneygram in these locations is to:

  • Retain and maintain customer traffic levels in the banking halls
  • Focus on efficient customer service due to dedicated service that excludes other core banking activities.
  • Providing customers with convenience, speed and ease.

According to him the UBA-Moneygram redshop which will enable customers spend less time in retreiving their monies, shall be replicated in new and up-coming branches across other regions of Ghana. Meanwhile all UBA branches continue to remain pay-out locations for Moneygram transfers.

 

30
June
UBA Takes Banking to the Border

Barely three (3) months after launching six branches in Accra, United Bank for Africa (Ghana) Ltd, a subsidiary of UBA Plc, which is the largest banking group in West-Africa, has unveiled a new set of four (4) ultra-modern and fully networked branches. This time around the bank has spread its tentacles to the border town of Aflao in the Volta region in its bid to provide affordable banking services for the un-banked and under-banked persons.

The remaining branches are located in East Legon, Dzorwulu and the Kaneshie market in Greater Accra. This brings to 16, the total number of branches UBA has established since entering the banking industry in 2005. On the average UBA has been opening branches at an average rate of one every two and half months.

This is in line with the bank’s roll out strategy which is aimed at developing a branch foot-print and delivery network that will ensure that the banks services are always within reach of valued customers.
Notable among the personalities that graced the launch ceremony was His Majesty Togbui Amenya Fiti V, Paramount Chief of the Aflao Traditional Area, Honourable Justice Kudjoe, Chief Executive Officer – Ketu District and other important personalities from the Immigration, CEPS and Police command.

Speaking at the formal launch at the Aflao branch at the border exit gate in Aflao, Nnamdi Okonkwo – Managing Director/ CEO mentioned that locating in Aflao presented UBA with a good opportunity to be closer to the doorstep of their target customers – traders, businesses, salaried and casual workers, sellers and shop owners. He added that UBA will continue its policy of opening new branches across the country and going by this strategy it will carry out its intention of opening another six (6) branches before close of this year.

The new branches will serve both retail and wholesale banking customers, consisting mainly of traders and business men/women who ply the sub-region with a comprehensive range of products. These include the traditional banking products and services with an emphasis on technology driven products/services delivered through an on-line real-time technology platform.

 

09
June
UBA Partners GBS in Bills Payment & Promotions

UBA PARTNERS GBS IN BILLS PAYMENT & PROMOTIONS In line with the bank’s commitment to ensure comfortable and secured banking and payment services for all Ghanaians, UBA Ghana has introduced a new payment solution for existing and prospective subscribers of GBS (Gateway Broadcasting Services).

This new payment platform now affords existing and potential customers the opportunity to subscribe to GBS - to ‘give a new life to their television’, and conveniently pay their subscription bills at any UBA branch location nationwide. The new payment solution by UBA has been designed with the customer in mind. Beginning the month of May 2008, the new service brings payment services to the doorstep of the Ghanaian public.

Commenting on the partnership, the Chief Operating Officer of UBA Ghana, Mr Sanusi Mudasiru, said that the bank’s superior IT infrastructure enables it to offer the most convenient and safest platform for payment of subscription bills. He mentioned that the UBA platform is highly automated with efficient transaction solutions. According to him, ‘our efficient platform is devoid of any manual manipulation and it enables the system to perform all sorts of validations such as ensuring the GBS customer’s account number id entered is updated same day on real time basis. In a similar deal, UBA has also partnered GBS for its current promotion which is running till July 15, 2008.

Under this partnership, potential customers can get connected to GBS by paying for a special offer price on dish, decoder, smartcard and installation at the nearest UBA branch. UBA Ghana is a subsidiary of United Bank for Africa Plc, which is the largest banking group in West Africa with a balance sheet of approximately US$15bn and more than 6 million customers across West Africa. UBA (Ghana) Limited is currently operating in 12 locations in Ghana – Accra, Tema, Kumasi and Takoradi.

May
UBA Partners Arsenal FC into West Africa

United Bank for Africa Plc, West Africa's largest financial services institution, has entered into an exclusive and strategic partnership deal with the English football giant, ARSENAL FOOTBALL CLUB. The deal, signed by officials of both institutions at the Emirates Stadium in London on Tuesday May 27, 2008, will see UBA and Arsenal collaborate on a variety of financial services and grassroots football development initiatives.

The financial services will include co-branded electronic payment solutions such as debit and credit cards for consumers in all West African locations where UBA currently operates. This partnership with Arsenal supports UBA?s commitment to developing grassroots football in Africa and the bank's strategy to spearhead the use of electronic banking products in the continent. ?African youths yearn for inspiration. They need to be inspired and given opportunities to nurture their talents and achieve their dreams of becoming successful football stars.

This strategic alliance and other UBA football related initiatives will go a long way towards achieving this," said Angela Nwabuoku, Executive Director, Products and Segment Banking, UBA. Arsenal has successfully developed a number of similar commercial and technical partnerships across the world but this represents the Club's first significant financial services partnership in the Africa continent.

''This partnership with UBA represents an exciting opportunity for us. We are aware that Arsenal has an exceptionally strong following in Africa and we look forward to working with the bank in the development of financial services and football at grassroots level. The partnership will enable us to develop a closer affiliation with our supporters and give many fans the opportunity to visit Emirates Stadium, receive Arsenal merchandise and win shirts signed by our first team squad. UBA and Arsenal are also committed to renovating pitches across West Africa. Initially twelve pitches in Nigeria will be laid with artificial surfaces providing a durable and lasting facility for local players and we'll also provide local support with visits to the region by our community coaches said Adrian Ford, Commercial Director at Arsenal. 

About United Bank for Africa Plc

United Bank for Africa (UBA) Plc is West Africa's largest financial services group with assets in excess of US$14 billion. Assenting to its brand positioning as Africa's global bank, UBA has full operations and presence in Nigeria, Ghana, Uganda, Cameroon, Cayman Islands, New York and London, and has been rapidly expanding into other African countries with start-ups in Liberia, Sierra Leone and Cote d'Ivoire.

Providing a full range of solutions and services to over six million customers spanning all market segments, customers are able to enjoy walk-in services through the bank?s expansive retail distribution network, and remote services through electronic channels such as U-Mobile (via mobile phones) and U-Direct (via the internet). With over 700 business offices, an ATM network of over 1000 in Nigeria and three million cards in circulation, UBA is leads in electronic
payments in the sub-region.

About Arsenal FC

Arsenal Football Club is one of the most successful clubs in English football, having won thirteen League titles and ten FA Cups. The London-based club enjoys a global following due to its rich history and exciting brand of football. In Nigeria, one of every five football lovers is a fan of Arsenal.

17
March
UBA opens 6 new branches

Mr Nnamdi Okonkwo, MD/CEO of UBA Ghana commisoned sixe (6) new branches of the bank at a short but impressive media briefing yesterday. This brings to 12, the total number of branches UBA has established since entering the banking industry in 2005.

The opening of the six new branches, forms part of the bank's strategy to expand its operations and branch network across the country. The new branches which are located in Accra include Ringroad, Spintex road, East Legon, Dzoruwlu, Teshie and Madina.

The new branches will serve both retail and wholesale banking customers with a comprehensive range of products. These include the traditional banking products and services with an emphasis on technology driven products/services delivered through an on-line real-time technology platform.

Speaking at the media launch, Mr Okonkwo noted that UBA Ghana aims to develop a branch foot-print and delivery network that will ensure that the banks services are always within reach of valued customers. He mentioned that as Africa’s global bank, UBA has been expanding from Nigeria where it has attained dominant status, to other parts of West, East and Central Africa.

It will be recalled that UBA recently opened in London as UBA Capital (Europe). This is coming after about two decades of operations in New York and presence in Cayman Islands. He mentioned furhter that these new set of six branches is the first batch of its second phase expansion. hat he said, would be supported with a roll-out of electronic channels such as Point of Sale Terminals and ATM's in line with the objectives of the Ghana Interbank Payment and Settlement System.

Members of the Ghanaian press had the opportunity to tour the Ring-road branch and observe the new model edifice designed with customers in mind.
 

11
February
UBA launches subsidiary in London

UBA Capital (Europe), the London-based investment banking and asset management affiliate of UBA Plc – West Africa's largest financial services institution – has formally commenced business following its official launch on Wednesday February 6, 2008 in London.

The impressive ceremony witnessed by UK and African business leaders, representatives of leading investment banking firms, clients in Europe and key players in the London and African financial markets, took place at the historic Duke of Wellington Arch, Hyde Park, London.

The birth of UBA Capital was the result of the substantial equity investment by UBA in Afrinvest Ltd, a privately owned investment banking firm in London specialising in African securities.
UBA Capital will act as an important addition to UBA's Pan African asset management business, providing international investors with access to investment opportunities across the African continent.

As Africa's global bank, UBA has been expanding from Nigeria where it has attained dominant status, to other parts of West, East and Central Africa. The London affiliate will further extend the Bank's presence outside Africa in addition to its operations in New York and the Cayman Islands.

"We are most delighted at the launch of UBA Capital. It marks a significant milestone for us as we leverage this platform for all transactions involving Africa and Africa-related businesses," Mr. Tony Elumelu, the Group Managing Director/CEO, UBA Plc, said.

UBA Plc is the largest banking group in West Africa with a balance sheet of approximately US$15bn and more than 6 million customers across the region.

 

05
February
UBA donates to the Police Service

As part of its business contribution to sustainable development in the country, UBA Ghana on Tuesday February 5, 2008 presented three(3) air-conditioner units worth GHc 1,500 to the Ghana Police Service in Accra.

Leading a delegation from the bank, the Divisional Head of Operations – Sanusi Mudasiru, mentioned that UBA Ghana is committed to contributing its quota to Ghana’s economic goals through the development of the community in which it operates. He said that the service which the Police provide to the public is indispensable and this calls for continual assistance in equipping them. He further noted that due to the safe environment which the Police has provided since it entered the Ghanaian banking industry three (3) years ago, UBA Ghana has been able to make significant contributions to various social groups.

Receiving the donation on behalf of the Ghana Police Service, the Inspector-General of Police Mr. P. K. Acheampong, thanked UBA Ghana for their kind gesture. He said that the air-conditioners will provide an enabling environment to facilitate the work of the Public Affairs unit of the Ghana Police Service. He encouraged banks in the country to invest in security equipments by employing the use of modern technology or partnering with the Police service to clamp down on the activities of fraudsters.

UBA Ghana is expected to open nine (9) new branches by the end of the first quarter as part of its branch roll-out strategy.
